data.name: textBoxTeamConnectionsPath.ToolTip
data.value: This is the path pointing to the selection of connection files created / managed by TEAM. There are typically more than one connection file, because each environment will have its own connection details.

data.name: textBoxTeamConfigurationPath.ToolTip
data.value: This is the path pointing to the selection of configuration files created / managed by TEAM. There are typically more than one configuration file, because each environment will have its own configuration.

data.name: textBoxTeamEnvironmentsFilePath.ToolTip
data.value:
This is the file path to the TEAM environments file, which contains an overview of the available environments. By default, upon start, a sample Development and Production environment are created by VDW. However, this path can also be set to point at an existing environments file managed by the TEAM application.
The environments file will populate the 'Active environment' combo box, and will drive selection of the configuration and connections file as these are dependent on the selected environment.
